author: abrown
msg: DERBY-2131: Use a privileged block when calling out to the JAXP parser
so that users running with a security manager can insert XML values
that reference external DTDs without encountering security exceptions.
This patch does not include any tests; however, relevant test cases
will be enabled as part of DERBY-1758.

msg: cleaning up the forms on index.jsp and form.jsp ... main motivation was to get rid of hte stylesheet param since it's pretty much worthless, but i also wanted to try and make the only options displayed on form.jsp things that were general enough to apply to any combination of request handler / response writer pair that comes out of the box ... i deliberatley didn't include all of the highlight and facet params however, because I wasworred that would make the page too cluttered.
